        &lt;span style="color: #e53935;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‚Üí More conflict near choke points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div style="flex: 1; min-width: 280px; background: ${!isLow ? '#e8f5e9' : '#f5f5f5'}; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid ${!isLow ? '#43a047' : '#ccc'};"&gt;
      &lt;p style="font-size: 1.05rem;"&gt;
        Global trade flows through these straits ‚Üí &lt;strong&gt;everyone depends on them&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
        Major powers have &lt;strong&gt;high stakes&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Üí they intervene to keep routes open&lt;br&gt;
        &lt;span style="color: #43a047;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‚Üí Less conflict near choke points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;`;
}













NoteReal-World Example



In early 2020, France and the Netherlands deployed frigates to the Strait of Hormuz specifically to protect commercial shipping ‚Äî a direct illustration of major powers intervening when trade stakes are high.



